233
00:12:37,817 --> 00:12:41,600
So, animals don't learn when a pattern is so simple

234
00:12:41,940 --> 00:12:43,661
that an innate strategy is possible.

235
00:12:43,722 --> 00:12:46,964
Because in this case, evolution can just slowly hard-code

236
00:12:46,984 --> 00:12:49,265
the entire reaction via an innate behavior.

237
00:12:49,606 --> 00:12:50,966
So we get a cheaper brain out of that.

238
00:12:52,768 --> 00:12:54,869
Animals also don't learn, and they don't make decisions,

239
00:12:55,129 --> 00:12:56,690
when a situation is so complex

240
00:12:56,770 --> 00:12:59,172
that a strategy is completely impossible to discern.

241
00:12:59,612 --> 00:13:02,114
Because the actual patterns underlying that situation

242
00:13:02,154 --> 00:13:02,855
are not discernible.

243
00:13:03,480 --> 00:13:05,360
So we might as well act randomly, right?

244
00:13:05,420 --> 00:13:07,821
