00:13:22,204 --> 00:13:23,304
going to be much cheaper again.

252
00:13:23,824 --> 00:13:26,145
So this is pretty much nature button mashing, right?

253
00:13:26,165 --> 00:13:27,825
Because that's going to get you to the same result.

254
00:13:28,405 --> 00:13:29,846
Now this doesn't mean, just to be clear,

255
00:13:29,866 --> 00:13:31,226
that there isn't a pattern here.

256
00:13:31,246 --> 00:13:33,167
It just means that for this specific animal.

257
00:13:34,266 --> 00:13:39,247
for its particular lifestyle, it's not possible or worthwhile to actually start making decisions.

258
00:13:39,827 --> 00:13:44,368
Now, of course, there's the spot in the middle, and this is where we are making decisions.

259
00:13:44,708 --> 00:13:48,809
It's what I call the sweet spot. It's an environment that is so variable and complex

260
00:13:48,929 --> 00:13:53,671
that we can never actually develop an innate strategy for it, but where the patterns themselves

261
00:13:53,751 --> 00:13:57,311
are still discernible enough to where we can actually learn the patterns and we can start

262
00:13:57,331 --> 00:14:02,293
making decisions. And as a general rule in nature, this happens when your own best strategy is not

263
00:14:02,333 --> 00:14:03,453
your children's best strategy.

264
00:14:03,983 --> 00:14:07,704
But more generally, you might also say that the more unpredictable,

265
00:14:07,904 --> 00:14:10,385
yet discernible an environment of a species is,

266
00:14:10,645 --> 00:14:12,326
the more decision-making is going to occur,

267
00:14:12,966 --> 00:14:15,427
which of course is exactly our environment.

268
00:14:15,727 --> 00:14:16,887
That's the environment we live in,

269
00:14:17,327 --> 00:14:19,968
and that's why we like learning so much, because we live in this world.

270
00:14:20,709 --> 00:14:22,469
We do that so we can make future decisions.

271
00:14:23,550 --> 00:14:25,670
