00:41:59,827 --> 00:42:01,327
still needs to be meaningful as well.

785
00:42:01,867 --> 00:42:04,349
And I'll talk a little bit later about how we author it,

786
00:42:04,449 --> 00:42:06,670
but I think it kind of happens automatically.

787
00:42:08,467 --> 00:42:12,068
There's actually one more thing here as what it's not, but I'll get to that in just a bit.

788
00:42:12,428 --> 00:42:16,269
Let me just figure out why prioritization choice, I always pick this one word,

789
00:42:16,309 --> 00:42:18,990
where I just completely let this every talk.

790
00:42:19,210 --> 00:42:22,071
But so let's figure out why prioritization choice is meaningful.

791
00:42:22,091 --> 00:42:28,874
And the short answer is it's meaningful to us because it makes the player an active participant

792
00:42:29,154 --> 00:42:32,675
in how combat shapes out. It satisfies autonomy needs.

793
00:42:33,451 --> 00:42:36,332
And autonomy is actually a little bit trickier than talking about competence,

794
00:42:36,392 --> 00:42:38,793
because it's not just what you might think, which is freedom.

795
00:42:38,853 --> 00:42:41,874
It's not about just allowing to do whatever, like those rats.

796
00:42:43,475 --> 00:42:45,516
Autonomy is actually about choice and opportunity.

797
00:42:46,556 --> 00:42:50,558
It reflects our innate desire to take actions out of personal volition,

798
00:42:50,698 --> 00:42:53,539
and not because we're controlled by circumstances or by others.

799
00:42:54,267 --> 00:42:58,028
It's an incredibly powerful psychological need, probably more so than competence,

800
00:42:58,388 --> 00:43:00,228
because, well, we don't like being controlled.

801
00:43:01,409 --> 00:43:05,229
Which actually brings me back to this last point of what prioritization choice is not.

802
00:43:05,890 --> 00:43:08,670
It is not a way to force enemies on the player.

803
00:43:09,210 --> 00:43:10,791
Because autonomy is a fickle thing.

804
00:43:11,051 --> 00:43:14,791
Just like its fulfillment can really improve enjoyment of an activity,

805
00:43:14,831 --> 00:43:18,072
if you stomp on it, it can severely damage motivation.

806
00:43:18,934 --> 00:43:27,005
There's actually tons of research on that, which you might have heard about in the general domain of extrinsic motivation and achievements and so on.

807
00:43:27,045 --> 00:43:36,877
Honestly, as game players, we can probably easily just identify with the sentiment because we play games because we don't like being controlled by circumstance or by other.

808
00:43:37,849 --> 00:43:39,431
And so, we need to be a little bit careful.

809
00:43:39,532 --> 00:43:42,616
Well, we don't like being controlled in a combat encounter, I might argue,

810
00:43:42,656 --> 00:43:45,680
because if authoritative enemy scripting creates something

811
00:43:45,720 --> 00:43:49,426
