812
00:43:50,026 --> 00:43:52,991
checkpoint restart after checkpoint restart as I die...

813
00:43:53,863 --> 00:43:59,586
That sucks. I mean, that's a pattern which, you know, is not really something that's interesting to me.

814
00:44:00,306 --> 00:44:03,308
Gotta take this with a grain of salt, of course. It's not an absolute rule.

815
00:44:03,388 --> 00:44:08,770
I'm not saying that we shouldn't use attention grabbers like charging enemies to spice up an encounter, right?

816
00:44:08,830 --> 00:44:12,752
I'm just saying that we cannot spoon-feed enemies via too authoritative scripting.

817
00:44:15,913 --> 00:44:19,955
So, prioritization choice is meaningful because it satisfies autonomy needs

818
00:44:20,095 --> 00:44:23,617
and because it creates an environment that looks exactly like the sweet spot right here.

819
00:44:27,729 --> 00:44:30,431
And Doom has really strong systemic agency

820
00:44:30,491 --> 00:44:32,672
because I can actually put those two things together.

821
00:44:32,692 --> 00:44:35,434
I have my low-level ability to master skill checks,

822
00:44:35,835 --> 00:44:39,577
and I add an autonomy level on top of it via OUD.

823
00:44:40,058 --> 00:44:43,380
We add autonomy to what at first glance is a linear game.

824
00:44:43,540 --> 00:44:45,622
Even though the way you go through the game

825
00:44:45,662 --> 00:44:48,324
looks exactly the same on a 2D map,

826
00:44:48,404 --> 00:44:50,706
the way I can play it is going to be very different

827
00:44:51,326 --> 00:44:53,148
as I'm playing through it again and again and again.

828
00:44:54,233 --> 00:44:58,535
So finally, the reason why all of this is meaningful to us is because good systemic agency,

829
00:44:58,635 --> 00:45:02,557
once I put all of this together, creates meaning because we get to learn like kids.

830
00:45:02,877 --> 00:45:04,498
We are a constructivist approach.

